  "question": "Indexing",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Indexing - Interactive Demonstration</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 24px; color: #111; background: #f7f9fc; }\n    h1 { margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 24px; }\n    p.lead { margin: 0 0 18px 0; color: #444; max-width: 70ch; }\n    .grid { display: grid; gap: 18px; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; align-items: start; }\n    .card { background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(18,30,50,0.06); }\n    .controls { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 8px; }\n    button { background: #2563eb; color: white; border: none; padding: 8px 10px; border-radius: 6px; cursor: pointer; }\n    button.secondary { background: #e2e8f0; color: #111; }\n    label { font-weight: 600; font-size: 13px; display:block; margin-bottom: 6px; }\n    input[type=\"text\"], input[type=\"number\"], select, textarea { width:100%; padding: 8px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid #d1d5db; }\n    .array-view { display:flex; gap:6px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:10px; }\n    .cell { min-width:36px; height:36px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; border-radius:6px; background:#eef2ff; color:#1e3a8a; font-weight:600; }\n    .cell.highlight { background:#fde68a; color:#92400e; box-shadow:0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.06) inset; }\n    pre { background:#0f172a; color:#e6eef8; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; overflow:auto; max-height:220px; }\n    .small { font-size:13px; color:#475569; }\n    .result { margin-top:10px; padding:10px; border-radius:6px; background:#f8fafc; border:1px dashed #e2e8f0; }\n    .log { font-family: monospace; white-space:pre-wrap; font-size:13px; color:#0f172a; }\n    .section-title { margin:0 0 8px 0; font-size:16px; }\n    .flex { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; }\n    .badge { background:#eef2ff; color:#1e3a8a; padding:4px 8px; border-radius:999px; font-weight:600; font-size:13px; }\n    .example-docs { display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:6px; margin-top:10px; }\n    .doc { padding:8px; border-radius:6px; background:#fff; border:1px solid #eef2ff; }\n    footer { margin-top:18px; font-size:13px; color:#6b7280; }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Indexing — interactive concepts</h1>\n  <p class=\"lead\">This page demonstrates common indexing concepts used in programming and search: array indexing (0 vs 1-based), using an index (map) to speed lookups vs linear scans, and building a simple inverted index for text search. Try the examples below.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"grid\">\n    <div class=\"card\" id=\"leftCol\">\n      <!-- Array Indexing -->\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Array Indexing (0-based vs 1-based)</h2>\n      <div class=\"small\">Arrays store values at numeric positions called indices. Different systems sometimes use different base indexes (0 or 1).</div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>Example array</label>\n        <div id=\"arrayDisplay\" class=\"array-view\"></div>\n\n        <div style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; margin-top:10px;\">\n          <div style=\"flex:1;\">\n            <label>Enter index to read</label>\n            <input id=\"indexInput\" type=\"number\" value=\"0\" />\n          </div>\n          <div style=\"min-width:160px;\">\n            <label>Index base</label>\n            <select id=\"indexBase\">\n              <option value=\"0\">0-based (common in JS)</option>\n              <option value=\"1\">1-based (some languages, conceptual)</option>\n            </select>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"controls\">\n          <button id=\"readIndexBtn\">Read value</button>\n          <button class=\"secondary\" id=\"shuffleArrayBtn\">Shuffle array</button>\n          <button class=\"secondary\" id=\"resetArrayBtn\">Reset array</button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div id=\"arrayResult\" class=\"result\" style=\"display:none;\"></div>\n      </div>\n\n      <!-- Index vs Linear Search -->\n      <hr style=\"margin:18px 0;\" />\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Index (Map) vs Linear Search</h2>\n      <div class=\"small\">We create many records and compare searching by scanning every item vs using an index (a Map) to jump directly to results.</div>\n\n      <label style=\"margin-top:10px;\">Dataset size (items)</label>\n      <input id=\"datasetSize\" type=\"number\" value=\"50000\" min=\"100\" max=\"200000\" step=\"100\" />\n\n      <div class=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n        <button id=\"generateDataBtn\">Generate dataset</button>\n        <button id=\"buildIndexBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Build name → ids index</button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n        <label>Search name (exact match)</label>\n        <input id=\"searchName\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"e.g. Alice\" />\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n        <button id=\"linearSearchBtn\">Linear scan</button>\n        <button id=\"indexedSearchBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Indexed search</button>\n        <button id=\"showSampleBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Show sample items</button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div id=\"searchResult\" class=\"result\" style=\"display:none;\"></div>\n\n      <!-- Inverted Index -->\n      <hr style=\"margin:18px 0;\" />\n      <h2 class=\"section-title\">Inverted Index (text search)</h2>\n      <div class=\"small\">An inverted index maps terms (words) to the documents that contain them. This is the building block for fast full-text search.</div>\n\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n        <label>Documents (editable)</label>\n        <div class=\"example-docs\" id=\"docsList\"></div>\n        <div class=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <button id=\"addDocBtn\">Add document</button>\n          <button id=\"buildInvertedBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Build inverted index</button>\n          <button id=\"clearInvertedBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Clear index</button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <label>Query (terms, space separated)</label>\n          <input id=\"queryInput\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"e.g. garden cat\" />\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:8px;\">\n          <button id=\"queryIndexedBtn\">Query using inverted index</button>\n          <button id=\"queryLinearBtn\" class=\"secondary\">Query by scanning docs</button>\n        </div>\n\n        <div id=\"invertedResult\" class=\"result\" style=\"display:none;\"></div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"card\" id=\"rightCol\">\n      <div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:10px; align-items:center;\">\n        <div>\n          <div class=\"badge\">Interactive</div>\n        </div>\n        <div class=\"small\">All code runs in your browser. Try different sizes and queries.</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <hr style=\"margin:12px 0;\" />\n\n      <h3 style=\"margin-top:0;\">Explanation & Quick Notes</h3>\n      <ul style=\"margin-top:6px;\">\n        <li><strong>Array indexing:</strong> Accessing arr[i] is O(1) because the location is computed from the base pointer + i × element-size.</li>\n        <li><strong>Linear scan:</strong> To find a value without an index you may check every item → O(n).</li>\n        <li><strong>Index (Map):</strong> A map from key → list of item locations lets you find matches in O(1) (average) for the lookup plus O(k) to return k matches.</li>\n        <li><strong>Inverted index:</strong> Maps each term → set/list of document ids. For multi-term queries you typically intersect postings lists.</li>\n      </ul>\n\n      <h3 style=\"margin-top:12px;\">Live log</h3>\n      <pre id=\"log\" class=\"log\">Ready.</pre>\n\n      <footer>\n        Tip: For realistic performance tests use large datasets, but your browser has limits. This demo keeps things safe.\n      </footer>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <script>\n    // Utilities\n    function log(msg) {\n      const el = document.getElementById('log');\n      el.textContent = new Date().toLocaleTimeString() + ' — ' + msg + '\\\\n' + el.textContent;\n    }\n\n    // SECTION 1: Array indexing demo\n    const baseArray = ['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H'];\n    let currentArray = baseArray.slice();\n\n    const arrayDisplay = document.getElementById('arrayDisplay');\n    const indexInput = document.getElementById('indexInput');\n    const indexBase = document.getElementById('indexBase');\n    const arrayResult = document.getElementById('arrayResult');\n\n    function renderArray() {\n      arrayDisplay.innerHTML = '';\n      currentArray.forEach((v, i) => {\n        const d = document.createElement('div');\n        d.className = 'cell';\n        d.textContent = v;\n        d.dataset.index = i;\n        arrayDisplay.appendChild(d);\n      });\n    }\n\n    function highlightCell(pos) {\n      const nodes = arrayDisplay.querySelectorAll('.cell');\n      nodes.forEach(n => n.classList.remove('highlight'));\n      if (pos >= 0 && pos < nodes.length) {\n        nodes[pos].classList.add('highlight');\n      }\n    }\n\n    document.getElementById('readIndexBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const base = Number(indexBase.value);\n      const raw = Number(indexInput.value);\n      const computed = raw - base;\n      arrayResult.style.display = 'block';\n      if (!Number.isFinite(raw)) {\n        arrayResult.textContent = 'Please enter a valid number.';\n        return;\n      }\n      if (computed < 0 || computed >= currentArray.length) {\n        arrayResult.textContent = `Index ${raw} (interpreted as ${computed}) is out of range.`;\n        highlightCell(-1);\n      } else {\n        arrayResult.textContent = `Index ${raw} (interpreted as ${computed}) → value: \"${currentArray[computed]}\"`;\n        highlightCell(computed);\n      }\n      log(`Read index: input=${raw}, base=${base}, computed=${computed}`);\n    });\n\n    document.getElementById('shuffleArrayBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {\n      // simple Fisher-Yates\n      for (let i = currentArray.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {\n        const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));\n        [currentArray[i], currentArray[j]] = [currentArray[j], currentArray[i]];\n      }\n      renderArray();\n      arrayResult.style.display = 'none';\n      log('Array shuffled.');\n    });\n    document.getElementById('resetArrayBtn').addEventListener('click', () => {\n      currentArray = baseArray.slice();\n      renderArray();\n      arrayResult.style.display = 'none';\n      log('Array reset.');\n    });\n\n    // initial\n    renderArray();\n\n    // SECTION 2: Index vs Linear Search\n    let dataset = [];\n    let nameIndex = null;\n\n    const datasetSizeInput = document.getElementById('datasetSize');\n    const generateDataBtn = document.getElementById('generateDataBtn');\n    const buildIndexBtn = document.getElementById('buildIndexBtn');\n    const searchNameInput = document.getElementById('searchName');\n    const linearSearchBtn = document.getElementById('linearSearchBtn');\n    const indexedSearchBtn = document.getElementById('indexedSearchBtn');\n    const showSampleBtn = document.getElementById('showSampleBtn');\n    const searchResult = document.getElementById('searchResult');\n\n    // helper to generate random names (small pool so duplicates exist)\n    const sampleNames = ['Alice','Bob','Charlie','Diana','Eve','Frank','Grace','Heidi','Ivan','Judy','Mallory','Niaj','Olivia','Peggy','Sybil','Trent','Victor','Walter'];\n\n    function generateDataset(n) {\n      const arr = new Array(n);\n      for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n        const name = sampleNames[Math.floor(Math.random() * sampleNames.length)];\n        arr[i] = { id: i, name, value: Math.floor(Math.random() * 1000000) };\n      }\n      return arr;\n    }\n\n    generateDataBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const n = Math.max(0, Math.floor(Number(datasetSizeInput.value) || 0));\n      if (n <= 0) {\n        alert('Enter a positive dataset size.');\n        return;\n      }\n      log(`Generating dataset with ${n} items...`);\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      dataset = generateDataset(n);\n      nameIndex = null;\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      searchResult.style.display = 'block';\n      searchResult.innerHTML = `Generated ${n} items in ${(t1 - t0).toFixed(2)} ms. Index cleared.`;\n      log(`Dataset generated (${n} items) in ${(t1 - t0).toFixed(2)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    buildIndexBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      if (!dataset || dataset.length === 0) {\n        alert('Create dataset first.');\n        return;\n      }\n      log('Building name → ids index...');\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      const idx = new Map();\n      for (const item of dataset) {\n        const list = idx.get(item.name);\n        if (list) list.push(item.id);\n        else idx.set(item.name, [item.id]);\n      }\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      nameIndex = idx;\n      searchResult.style.display = 'block';\n      searchResult.innerHTML = `Built index for ${idx.size} unique names in ${(t1 - t0).toFixed(2)} ms.`;\n      log(`Index built (${idx.size} keys) in ${(t1 - t0).toFixed(2)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    function linearSearch(name) {\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      const result = [];\n      for (const item of dataset) {\n        if (item.name === name) result.push(item);\n      }\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      return { items: result, time: t1 - t0 };\n    }\n\n    linearSearchBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const q = (searchNameInput.value || '').trim();\n      if (!q) { alert('Enter a name to search.'); return; }\n      if (!dataset || dataset.length === 0) { alert('Generate dataset first.'); return; }\n      log(`Linear scan for \"${q}\"...`);\n      const { items, time } = linearSearch(q);\n      searchResult.style.display = 'block';\n      searchResult.innerHTML = `Linear scan: found ${items.length} items in ${time.toFixed(2)} ms. (Scanned ${dataset.length} items)`;\n      log(`Linear scan for \"${q}\" returned ${items.length} items in ${time.toFixed(2)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    indexedSearchBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const q = (searchNameInput.value || '').trim();\n      if (!q) { alert('Enter a name to search.'); return; }\n      if (!dataset || dataset.length === 0) { alert('Generate dataset first.'); return; }\n      if (!nameIndex) { alert('Build the index first.'); return; }\n      log(`Indexed lookup for \"${q}\"...`);\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      const ids = nameIndex.get(q) || [];\n      // retrieve items by id (direct array access)\n      const items = ids.map(id => dataset[id]);\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      searchResult.style.display = 'block';\n      searchResult.innerHTML = `Indexed lookup: found ${items.length} items in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(4)} ms. (Index lookup + retrieving ${items.length} items)`;\n      log(`Indexed lookup for \"${q}\" returned ${items.length} items in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(4)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    showSampleBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      if (!dataset || dataset.length === 0) { alert('Generate dataset first.'); return; }\n      const sample = dataset.slice(0, 12);\n      searchResult.style.display = 'block';\n      searchResult.innerHTML = '<strong>Sample items (first 12):</strong><br>' + sample.map(s => `id:${s.id} name:${s.name} value:${s.value}`).join('<br>');\n    });\n\n    // SECTION 3: Inverted index for text search\n    let docs = [\n      { id: 0, title: 'The garden cat', body: 'A small cat naps in the garden under a lemon tree.' },\n      { id: 1, title: 'City life', body: 'Busy streets, cafes, and tall buildings define city life.' },\n      { id: 2, title: 'Gardening tips', body: 'How to prune roses and prepare soil for spring.' },\n      { id: 3, title: 'Cat care', body: 'Nutrition and vet advice for your cat companion.' },\n    ];\n    let inverted = null;\n\n    const docsListEl = document.getElementById('docsList');\n    const addDocBtn = document.getElementById('addDocBtn');\n    const buildInvertedBtn = document.getElementById('buildInvertedBtn');\n    const clearInvertedBtn = document.getElementById('clearInvertedBtn');\n    const queryInput = document.getElementById('queryInput');\n    const queryIndexedBtn = document.getElementById('queryIndexedBtn');\n    const queryLinearBtn = document.getElementById('queryLinearBtn');\n    const invertedResult = document.getElementById('invertedResult');\n\n    function renderDocs() {\n      docsListEl.innerHTML = '';\n      for (const d of docs) {\n        const container = document.createElement('div');\n        container.className = 'doc';\n        container.innerHTML = `\n          <div style=\"display:flex; justify-content:space-between; gap:8px;\">\n            <input data-id=\"${d.id}\" data-field=\"title\" value=\"${escapeHtml(d.title)}\" />\n            <button class=\"secondary\" data-action=\"delete\" data-id=\"${d.id}\">Delete</button>\n          </div>\n          <textarea data-id=\"${d.id}\" data-field=\"body\">${escapeHtml(d.body)}</textarea>\n        `;\n        docsListEl.appendChild(container);\n      }\n      // attach listeners for edits / deletes\n      docsListEl.querySelectorAll('input, textarea').forEach(el => {\n        el.addEventListener('input', (ev) => {\n          const id = Number(el.dataset.id);\n          const field = el.dataset.field;\n          const doc = docs.find(x => x.id === id);\n          if (doc) doc[field] = el.value;\n        });\n      });\n      docsListEl.querySelectorAll('button[data-action=\"delete\"]').forEach(btn => {\n        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n          const id = Number(btn.dataset.id);\n          docs = docs.filter(x => x.id !== id);\n          renderDocs();\n        });\n      });\n    }\n\n    function escapeHtml(s) {\n      return s.replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;');\n    }\n\n    addDocBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const id = docs.length ? Math.max(...docs.map(d => d.id)) + 1 : 0;\n      docs.push({ id, title: `Doc ${id}`, body: `This is an example document number ${id}.` });\n      renderDocs();\n      log(`Added doc ${id}`);\n    });\n\n    function tokenize(text) {\n      return (text || '')\n        .toLowerCase()\n        .replace(/[^a-z0-9\\\\s]/g, ' ')\n        .split(/\\\\s+/)\n        .filter(Boolean);\n    }\n\n    buildInvertedBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      log('Building inverted index for documents...');\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      const idx = new Map();\n      for (const doc of docs) {\n        const terms = new Set([...tokenize(doc.title), ...tokenize(doc.body)]);\n        for (const term of terms) {\n          const list = idx.get(term);\n          if (list) list.push(doc.id);\n          else idx.set(term, [doc.id]);\n        }\n      }\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      inverted = idx;\n      invertedResult.style.display = 'block';\n      invertedResult.innerHTML = `Built inverted index with ${idx.size} unique terms in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(2)} ms.`;\n      log(`Inverted index built (${idx.size} terms) in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(2)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    clearInvertedBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      inverted = null;\n      invertedResult.style.display = 'block';\n      invertedResult.innerHTML = 'Inverted index cleared.';\n      log('Inverted index cleared.');\n    });\n\n    queryIndexedBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const q = (queryInput.value || '').trim();\n      if (!q) { alert('Enter query terms.'); return; }\n      if (!inverted) { alert('Build inverted index first.'); return; }\n      const terms = tokenize(q);\n      if (terms.length === 0) return;\n      log(`Indexed query for terms: ${terms.join(', ')}`);\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      // retrieve postings lists\n      let postings = terms.map(t => (inverted.get(t) || []));\n      // intersect postings lists (simple method)\n      postings.sort((a,b) => a.length - b.length);\n      let answer = postings.length ? postings[0].slice() : [];\n      for (let i = 1; i < postings.length; i++) {\n        const setB = new Set(postings[i]);\n        answer = answer.filter(x => setB.has(x));\n      }\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      invertedResult.style.display = 'block';\n      invertedResult.innerHTML = `Indexed query returned ${answer.length} documents in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(4)} ms.<br>` +\n        (answer.length ? answer.map(id => `• [${id}] ${docs.find(d=>d.id===id).title}`).join('<br>') : '(no matches)');\n      log(`Indexed query matched ${answer.length} docs in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(4)}ms`);\n    });\n\n    queryLinearBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n      const q = (queryInput.value || '').trim();\n      if (!q) { alert('Enter query terms.'); return; }\n      const terms = tokenize(q);\n      if (terms.length === 0) return;\n      log(`Linear query for terms: ${terms.join(', ')}`);\n      const t0 = performance.now();\n      const results = [];\n      for (const doc of docs) {\n        const tokens = new Set(tokenize(doc.title + ' ' + doc.body));\n        let ok = true;\n        for (const term of terms) {\n          if (!tokens.has(term)) { ok = false; break; }\n        }\n        if (ok) results.push(doc.id);\n      }\n      const t1 = performance.now();\n      invertedResult.style.display = 'block';\n      invertedResult.innerHTML = `Linear query returned ${results.length} documents in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(2)} ms.<br>` +\n        (results.length ? results.map(id => `• [${id}] ${docs.find(d=>d.id===id).title}`).join('<br>') : '(no matches)');\n      log(`Linear query matched ${results.length} docs in ${(t1-t0).toFixed(2)}ms (scanned ${docs.length} docs)`);\n    });\n\n    // initial render docs\n    renderDocs();\n\n    // Initial log\n    log('Demo ready: array, dataset, and inverted index sections initialized.');\n  </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
